Windows Commands 

Win + R → ncpa.cpl (Network Connections Panel. Control Panel Library)
Win + R → sysdm.cpl (System Properties Device Manager. Control Panel Library)

Search for a file by name (fastest)
cmd> dir C:\ /s /b | findstr /i "<filename>"
cmd> dir C:\ /s /b | C:\Windows\System32\findstr.exe /i "x64dbg*"		# if PATH variable is messed up
• /s → search subdirectories
• /b → bare output (full paths only)
• findstr /i → case‑insensitive match
			cmd> where /R C:\ *obsidian*
			C:\Users\bbt12\Downloads\Obsidian-1.11.7.exe
						/R = Recursive
PS> Get-ChildItem -Path C:\ -Recurse -Filter "*filename*" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object FullName

Search for a file by extension
cmd> dir C:\*.txt /s /b

Search Strings → output file contain the string
cmd> findstr /s /i /m "<text_to_search>" C:\*.*
cmd> findstr /s /i /m "sqlftp" C:\*.*
• /m → only show filenames
• /s → recursive
• /i → case‑insensitive

Search File Using where (built‑in search)
cmd> where /r C:\ <filename>
cmd> where /r C:\ sqlftp.txt

Decode Base64 strings
PS> [System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetString([System.Convert]::FromBase64String("SGVsbG8gd29ybGQ="))

Add an Exclusion = To keep Windows Defender from eating your tools or blocking your builds
PS > Add-MpPreference -ExclusionPath "C:\Users\student\Desktop\BVT-Tools"
To verify it worked, you can list your exclusions with:
PS > Get-MpPreference | Select-Object -ExpandProperty ExclusionPath

Grep string “SID” in first 20 line of yourfile.txt
PS> Get-Content .\yourfile.txt -TotalCount 20 | Select-String "SID"

